   373	
   374	## 4. Plugin Loading Mechanism
   375	
   376	### 4.1 Single Owner: PipelineLoader
   377	
   378	**Critical design rule:** `PipelineLoader` owns all plugin discovery. The
   379	`Orchestrator` consumes the already-validated registry from `PipelineSpec`.
   380	No duplicated loading, no ambiguity about when validation happens.
   381	
   382	```
   383	pipeline.yaml parsed by PipelineLoader.load()
   384	    │
   385	    ├─ 1. Parse YAML via yaml.safe_load()
   386	    ├─ 2. Schema migration (existing)
   387	    ├─ 3. Parse cli_plugins: → PluginRegistry with CLIPluginRunner instances
   388	    ├─ 4. Parse python_plugins: → only if --allow-python-plugins
   389	    │       ├─ Resolve search_paths → find <module>.py
   390	    │       ├─ importlib to load module with unique sys.modules key
   391	    │       ├─ issubclass check against UnisonPlugin
   392	    │       ├─ validate_installation() → (ok, err)
   393	    │       └─ Instantiate → store in registry
   394	    ├─ 5. Resolve valid runtimes = BUILTIN_RUNTIMES ∪ registry.names()
   395	    ├─ 6. _build_agents() validates each agent.runtime ∈ valid
   396	    ├─ 7. PipelineSpec stores the validated PluginRegistry
   397	    │
   398	    └─ Orchestrator.__init__()
   399	           └─ self._plugin_registry = spec.plugin_registry  # consume, don't reload
   400	```
   401	
