     1	# Unison Plugin System — Design & Specification
     2	
     3	**Status:** Draft, Phase 10 Round 2
     4	**Author:** Architect (Claude Code)
     5	**Target:** Unison v2.1
     6	
     7	---
     8	
     9	## 1. Motivation
    10	
    11	Unison currently hardcodes four agent runtimes via a `Literal` type alias:
    12	
    13	```python
    14	# interfaces.py:38 — the bottleneck
    15	Runtime: TypeAlias = Literal["claude", "codex", "hermes", "openclaw"]
    16	```
    17	
    18	Adding a new agent CLI (Gemini CLI, GitHub Copilot, a custom bash script wrapping an
    19	in-house model, etc.) requires editing 5 source files. This is a **closed set**. The
    20	plugin system makes it **open** — users declare a new runtime with a 6-line YAML
    21	stanza, no source edits needed.
    22	
    23	### Design Goals (ranked)
    24	
    25	1. **Safe by default.** A declarative YAML-only path covers 90% of use cases
    26	   (gemini, copilot, custom bash wrappers) without writing or importing Python.
    27	2. **Extensible for power users.** An opt-in Python plugin API supports non-CLI
    28	   backends (HTTP APIs, gRPC, WebSocket agents).
    29	3. **Pre-flight validation.** All plugin errors surface before any agent runs.
    30	4. **Mechanical backward compatibility.** Existing `pipeline.yaml` files load
    31	   identically. Existing runners are untouched.
    32	
    33	---
    34	
    35	## 2. Two-Tier Plugin Architecture
    36	
    37	The design splits into two tiers with a hard trust boundary between them.
    38	
    39	### Tier 1: Declarative CLI Plugins (Always Available)
    40	
    41	A `cli_plugins:` YAML section where the user declares `binary`, `args`, `env`, and
    42	`timeout_grace`. No Python code is loaded — the orchestrator wraps the binary via
    43	`subprocess.run` directly using a built-in `CLIPluginRunner`.
    44	
    45	**This is the recommended path for all CLI-based runtimes** (Gemini, Copilot,
    46	custom bash scripts, etc.). It covers the common case with zero trust risk.
    47	
    48	### Tier 2: Python Plugin API (Opt-in via `--allow-python-plugins`)
    49	
    50	A `UnisonPlugin` ABC in `src/unison/plugins/base.py`. Users write a Python class,
    51	drop it in `~/.unison/plugins/`, and declare it in `python_plugins:`. Loading
    52	Python plugins requires an explicit CLI flag. This gate prevents a pipeline from
    53	an untrusted repo from executing arbitrary Python during validation.
    54	
    55	---
    56	
    57	## 3. Plugin Interface
    58	
    59	### 3.1 Declarative CLI Plugin (YAML Schema)
    60	
    61	```yaml
    62	# pipeline.yaml
    63	version: "2.1"
    64	project_root: "."
    65	
    66	# ── Declarative CLI plugins (Tier 1, always safe) ─────────────────────────
    67	cli_plugins:
    68	  gemini:
    69	    binary: gemini-internal
    70	    args: ["-p", "--output-format", "text", "-y"]
    71	    env:
    72	      GEMINI_API_KEY: "${GEMINI_API_KEY}"
    73	      GEMINI_MODEL: "gemini-2.5-pro"
    74	    timeout_grace: 10
    75	
    76	  custom-script:
    77	    binary: /opt/scripts/my-agent.sh
    78	    args: ["--model", "ft-v3", "--format", "markdown"]
    79	    env:
    80	      API_KEY: "${MY_API_KEY}"
    81	    timeout_grace: 2
    82	
    83	# ── Python plugins (Tier 2, requires --allow-python-plugins) ──────────────
    84	python_plugins:
    85	  # Defined here but NOT loaded unless CLI flag is set
    86	  openclaw-v2:
    87	    module: openclaw_runner
    88	    class: OpenClawV2Plugin
    89	    search_paths:
    90	      - ~/.unison/plugins
    91	    kwargs:
    92	      endpoint: "https://api.internal/openclaw/v2"
    93	      pool_size: 4
    94	
    95	# ── Agents (unchanged) ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    96	agents:
    97	  planner:
    98	    role: architect
    99	    runtime: claude                    # built-in: unchanged
   100	    model: opus-4.8
   101	    system_prompt_path: "prompts/architect.md"
   102	    pipeline_role: planner
   103	
   104	  coder:
   105	    role: developer
   106	    runtime: gemini                    # <-- declarative CLI plugin
   107	    model: gemini-2.5-pro
   108	    system_prompt_path: "prompts/developer.md"
   109	    pipeline_role: developer
